column59: Q24_1:Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program (SNAP)SNAP provides nutrition benefits to supplement the food budget of needy families so they can purchase healthy food and move towards self-sufficiency. (fns.usda.gov)
column60: Q24_2:Temporary Assistance for Needy Families (TANF)A program that provides grant funds to states and territories to provide families with financial assistance and related support services. State-administered programs may include childcare assistance, job preparation, and work assistance. (benefits.gov)
column61: Q24_3:Women Infant and Children (WIC)A program provides foods, health care referrals, and nutrition education for low-income women, infants, and children up to age five who are found to be at nutritional risk. (fns.usda.gov)
column62: Q24_4:MedicaidA health insurance program which provides coverage to eligible low-income adults, children, pregnant women, elderly, and people with disabilities. (medicaid.gov)
column63: Q24_5:Social Security Income (SSI)Monthly benefits to people with limited income and resources who are disabled, blind, or age 65 or older. (ssa.gov
column64: Q24_6:Social Security- Disability BenefitsBenefits provided to individuals who are unable to work due to their medical condition, which is expected to last at least one year or result in death. (ssa.gov)
column65: Q24_7:Military/ Veteran ServicesBenefits such as financial and other forms of assistance provided to veterans, their dependents, and survivors. (va.gov)
column66: Q24_8:Unemployment BenefitsFinancial support for individuals that lost their job and meet eligibility requirements. (twc.texas.gov)
